ation inc a nonprofit organization privacy policy about wikipedia disclaimers contact wikipedia developers cookie statement mobile view mack trucks  wikipedia mack trucks from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search for other uses see mack disambiguation mack trucks inc type subsidiary of the volvo group industry automotive founded june   headquarters greensboro north carolina united states key people dennis slagle president products heavy and mediumduty trucks parent volvo website macktruckscom mack trucks inc is an american truck–manufacturing company and a former manufacturer of buses and trolley buses founded in  as the mack brothers company it manufactured its first truck in  and adopted its present name in  mack trucks is a subsidiary of ab volvo which purchased mack along with renault trucks in  after being founded in brooklyn new york the companys headquarters were in allentown pennsylvania from  to  when they moved to greensboro north carolina the entire line of mack products is still produced in macungie pennsylvania with additional assembly plants in pennsylvania maryland australia and venezuela contents  operations   restructuring plan  history  corporation timeline  market model and products timeline  products  current models  north america  australia new zealand and south africa  fire apparatus products  fire apparatus gallery  previous models  ac  n series  b models  rrbrdrlrmrw u dmdmm models  engines  other products  trademark  leadership  military models  world war ii  post world war ii  notable appearances in media  see also  references  external links operationsedit currently the companys manufacturing facilities are located at the macungie assembly operations plant in lower macungie township pennsylvania mack trucks is one of the top producers in the vocational and onroad vehicle market class  through class  it is also one of the most popular manufacturers of heavyduty offroad trucks in the united statescitation needed mack trucks have been sold in  countries the macungie pennsylvania manufacturing plant located near its former allentown corporate headquarters produces all mack products the mack mpseries engine mack transmissions the tc transfer cases and rear engine power takeoffs are designed and manufactured in hagerstown maryland which according to local historians was the original factory locationcitation needed parts for macks righthanddrive vehicles are produced in brisbane australia for worldwide distribution assembly for south america is done at mack de venezuela ca in caracas venezuela the venezuela operation is a complete knock down ckd facility components are shipped from the united states to caracas and the plant then does the final assembly in addition to its macungie manufacturing facility mack also has a remanufacturing center in middletown pennsylvania where it takes used parts and refurbishes them for resale and reuse  restructuring planedit on august   mack trucks announced a major restructuring plan that included relocation of macks head office product development most support functions and purchasing functions to greensboro north carolina in  macks parent volvo trucks already has its north american base in greensboro assembly of all produced mack highway vehicles in macungie pennsylvania from  macks testing facility in allentown pennsylvania being converted into a customer demonstrationreception center in  restructuring the parts distribution network by  later delayed to first quarter ° historyedit corporation timelineedit this is a timeline of mack trucks history most of the information is taken from the mack history page at macktruckscom unless otherwise noted early bus mack truck used to carry ore at the acosta mine museum in real del monte hidalgo state mexico mack acmodel flatbed delivery truck at the petersen automotive museum the hale inch mirror for mount wilson observatory on its way up the mount wilson toll road on a mack truck in  this  mack truck that has been restored and is on display at the yrc freight headquarters in overland park kansas mack x nmodel to ton wrecker photo dated  may  national archives co olivedrabcom mack no artillery tractor b model – a mack cdt bus built in  r series –  mc fire engine –  john m jack mack gets a job at fallesen  berry a carriage and wagon company in brooklyn new york  john mack and his brother augustus f gus mack buy the company john worked for  a third mack brother william c mack joins his brothers in the companys operations the macks try working with steam powered and electric motor cars s inspired by orville and wilbur wright willis carrier and henry fords inventions john mack has a vision of producing heavy duty trucks and engines  the macks open their first bus manufacturing plant the mack bus ordered by a sightseeing company is delivered  the mack brothers company established in new york  the company introduces the name manhattan on its products  allentown selected as the home of main manufacturing operations and headquarters a fourth mack brother joseph mack becomes a stockholder mack begins making rail cars and locomotives  the manhattan trucks are since known as mack trucks charles mack a fifth mack brother joins the company  the saurer motor truck company headed by cp coleman had the rights to manufacture and sell heavy trucks under the saurer brand name at its plant in plainfield new jersey on september   the saurer motor truck company merged with the mack brothers motor car company of allentown headed by j m mack to form the international motor truck company imtc imtc would continue to make and sell trucks using the saurer name until  the capitalization of imtc was  million total m for saurer or  and m for mack brothers  brothers john and joseph mack leave  the united states army conducts a transcontinental project using mack trucks to study the need for national highway systems  the company name is changed to mack trucks inc the bulldog is accepted as the companys corporate symbol  john mack dies in a car crash in weatherly pennsylvania  while recuperating from an operation alfred fellows masury macks chief engineer carved the first bulldog hood ornament masury applied for and received a patent for his design the bulldog ornament has adorned mack trucks ever since  mack trucks helps in the building of many american structures including the hoover dam  fire apparatus manufacturing moved from allentown pennsylvania to long island city new york in queens  fire apparatus manufacturing moved back to allentown pennsylvania from long island city new york  mack trucks inc buys brockway motor company brockway ceases in   mack begins production at its assembly plant in oakville ontario canada the facility closed in   mack trucks becomes a part of the signal oil and gas company in a oneforone exchange for cumulative convertible preferred stock later that year signal changes its name to the signal companies inc  mack moves into its new allentown world headquarters  renault buys  of mack trucks inc  renault increases ownership stake to  signal lowers its stake to   mack trucks conducts an ipo and issues  million shares of common stock renault increases holdings to  while signal reduces its stake to   renault reorganizes renault véhicules industriels buys renaults mack shares  mack trucks becomes a wholly owned subsidiary of renault véhicules industriels when remaining publicly traded shares acquired at  per share  mack together with renault véhicules industriels becomes part of volvo ab of sweden the parent company renault s a receives a  stake in the combined company in  renault véhicules industriels changes its name to renault trucks  mack has a record sale year  mack announces relocation of corporate headquarters to greensboro north carolina market model and products timelineedit this is a timeline of mack trucks history most of the information is taken from the mack history page at macktruckscom unless otherwise noted photos of most mo