erences  external links operationsedit currently the companys manufacturing facilities are located at the macungie assembly operations plant in lower macungie township pennsylvania mack trucks is one of the top producers in the vocational and onroad vehicle market class  through class  it is also one of the most popular manufacturers of heavyduty offroad trucks in the united statescitation needed mack trucks have been sold in  countries the macungie pennsylvania manufacturing plant located near its former allentown corporate headquarters produces all mack products the mack mpseries engine mack transmissions the tc transfer cases and rear engine power takeoffs are designed and manufactured in hagerstown maryland which according to local historians was the original factory locationcitation needed parts for macks righthanddrive vehicles are produced in brisbane australia for worldwide distribution assembly for south america is done at mack de venezuela ca in caracas venezuela the venezuela operation is a complete knock down ckd facility components are shipped from the united states to caracas and the plant then does the final assembly in addition to its macungie manufacturing facility mack also has a remanufacturing center in middletown pennsylvania where it takes used parts and refurbishes them for resale and reuse  restructuring planedit on august   mack trucks announced a major restructuring plan that included relocation of macks head office product development most support functions and purchasing functions to greensboro north carolina in  macks parent volvo trucks already has its north american base in greensboro assembly of all produced mack highway vehicles in macungie pennsylvania from  macks testing facility in allentown pennsylvania being converted into a customer demonstrationreception center in  restructuring the parts distribution network by  later delayed to first quarter ° historyedit corporation timelineedit this is a timeline of mack trucks history most of the information is taken from the mack history page at macktruckscom unless otherwise noted early bus mack truck used to carry ore at the acosta mine museum in real del monte hidalgo state mexico mack acmodel flatbed delivery truck at the petersen automotive museum the hale inch mirror for mount wilson observatory on its way up the mount wilson toll road on a mack truck in  this  mack truck that has been restored and is on display at the yrc freight headquarters in overland park kansas mack x nmodel to ton wrecker photo dated  may  national archives co olivedrabcom mack no artillery tractor b model – a mack cdt bus built in  r series –  mc fire engine –  john m jack mack gets a job at fallesen  berry a carriage and wagon company in brooklyn new york  john mack and his brother augustus f gus mack buy the company john worked for  a third mack brother william c mack joins his brothers in the companys operations the macks try working with steam powered and electric motor cars s inspired by orville and wilbur wright willis carrier and henry fords inventions john mack has a vision of producing heavy duty trucks and engines  the macks open their first bus manufacturing plant the mack bus ordered by a sightseeing company is delivered  the mack brothers company established in new york  the company introduces the name manhattan on its products  allentown selected as the home of main manufacturing operations and headquarters a fourth mack brother joseph mack becomes a stockholder mack begins making rail cars and locomotives  the manhattan trucks are since known as mack trucks charles mack a fifth mack brother joins the company  the saurer motor truck company headed by cp coleman had the rights to manufacture and sell heavy trucks under the saurer brand name at its plant in plainfield new jersey on september   the saurer motor truck company merged with the mack brothers motor car company of allentown headed by j m mack to form the international motor truck company imtc imtc would continue to make and sell trucks using the saurer name until  the capitalization of imtc was  million total m for saurer or  and m for mack brothers  brothers john and joseph mack leave  the united states army conducts a transcontinental project using mack trucks to study the need for national highway systems  the company name is changed to mack trucks inc the bulldog is accepted as the companys corporate symbol  john mack dies in a car crash in weatherly pennsylvania  while recuperating from an operation alfred fellows masury macks chief engineer carved the first bulldog hood ornament masury applied for and received a patent for his design the bulldog ornament has adorned mack trucks ever since  mack trucks helps in the building of many american structures including the hoover dam  fire apparatus manufacturing moved from allentown pennsylvania to long island city new york in queens  fire apparatus manufacturing moved back to allentown pennsylvania from long island city new york  mack trucks inc buys brockway motor company brockway ceases in   mack begins production at its assembly plant in oakville ontario canada the facility closed in   mack trucks becomes a part of the signal oil and gas company in a oneforone exchange for cumulative convertible preferred stock later that year signal changes its name to the signal companies inc  mack moves into its new allentown world headquarters  renault buys  of mack trucks inc  renault increases ownership stake to  signal lowers its stake to   mack trucks conducts an ipo and issues  million shares of common stock renault increases holdings to  while signal reduces its stake to   renault reorganizes renault véhicules industriels buys renaults mack shares  mack trucks becomes a wholly owned subsidiary of renault véhicules industriels when remaining publicly traded shares acquired at  per share  mack together with renault véhicules industriels becomes part of volvo ab of sweden the parent company renault s a receives a  stake in the combined company in  renault véhicules industriels changes its name to renault trucks  mack has a record sale year  mack announces relocation of corporate headquarters to greensboro north carolina market model and products timelineedit this is a timeline of mack trucks history most of the information is taken from the mack history page at macktruckscom unless otherwise noted photos of most models – available at  a junior model  ton truck is introduced  mack delivers the first motorized hook and ladder firetruck used by the city of morristown new jersey  the mack abs are introduced  the mack acs are introduced ultimately over  of these models are sold world war i mack delivers over  trucks both to the united states and britains military a legend surfaces that british soldiers would call for mack bulldogs to be sent when facing adversity  mack becomes the first manufacturer to apply air cleaners and oil filters to their trucks  mack trucks are the first with power brakes on their trucks  mack introduces first truck with drive shaft instead of chain  model ab  international motors company develops gasolinedriven passenger railcar for the new york new haven and hartford railroad a standard passenger railcar on top of a standard motor truck chassis seating between  and  passengers at a cost of  the car operates in a tenmile  km stretch between new haven and derby connecticut  macks bj and bb models built  the bulldog starts to travel on the hoods of mack trucks  production of electric trolley coaches began continuing only until  a total of  trolley buses were built with portland oregon being by far the biggest customer with  total  the mack e series introduced mack jr trucks introduced  mack trucks is the first company to produce its own heavyduty diesel engines world war ii mack trucks were used by the military in various capacities and the company built many heavyduty trucks to help the allied forces win the day from  to  the combined armed forces of the united states great britain france and canada took delivery of  total vehicles the combat n series nb nju nm no nr etc accounted for  of the total commercial type vehicles including trucks offhighway firetrucks trailers and buses accounted for the rest a total of  no models alone were produced from  to  the  ton x no was the most important specifically military model and could be used as a transport or tractor for the  mm long tom field gun mack also built over  power trains for tanks the allentown bus plant c built vultee pby catalina flying boats as well as components for the bt valiant trainer and b liberator bombers more than  nju to ton x models were in the hands of the us army by  in    the french and british received several hundred nr and exbu models mack trucks ranked rd among united states corporations in the value of world war ii military production contracts  l model series introduced continuing until   the mack a model series of trucks is introduced produced until   the mack b model series of trucks is introduced  produced until   the d model low cab forward city delivery truck entered the market access to the engine compartment was possible by the vertilift cab the cab lifted straight up hydraulically guided by a forklift style mast behind the cab two styles of d models were produced the first styling had a square grille and no dress up trim it was produced in  and early  the second styling included a styled grille cab rear corner windows and stylish emblems and trim the second styling was built from mid  until the end of the d model in  a total of  d model mack trucks were produced from  until   the military m  ton x semi tractor went into production developed from the no it would be the us armys standard until replaced by the m starting in   mack buys the tooling of the ahrensfox fire engine co and introduced the mack c model cab forward fire engine which was an ahrensfox design and the first of the cincinnati cabs  later built by the truck cab manufacturing co an oem vendor builder of cincinnati ohio that have been the staple of the american fire service to this day  the first aluminum rivetted construction coe caboverengine family of trucks is introduced the g model which had a short production due to a striking resemblance to the kenworth coe and mack having the f model ready for productioncitation needed a total of  g model  city of hamilton bermuda buys first mack built dieselpower fire truck in a b model chassis  the second of the coe caboverengine family of trucks is introduced the f model all steel sleeper fl or non sleeper f is the first of this family of models for mack  mack releases the super pumper system to be used by the new york city fire department it would help put out  fires  the r model series introduced to replace the b model series some r series models continue in production until   the rl for rwestern model built at hayward california until   the cf model fire engine introduced replacing the c model the cf was a cab forward adaptation of the cab over style commercial f model cab  mack patents the cab air suspension  macungie plant opens build the cruiseliner series until   superliner introduced production runs for years until   introduction of the lowcabforward urban mcmr series  mediumduty model midliner introduced built by renault véhicules industriels in france this lighter truck filled a gap at the lower end of macks spectrum as they were almost unrepresented in the class  segment before the introduction of the midliner the smallest engine made by mack had been the  hp diesel inlinesix etz   production of the mh ultraliner model begins  mack introduces the ch series for highway applications  e engine replaces e engine  fire apparatus production ends  mack introduces the le low entry refuse vehicle  electronic unit pump eup replaces electronic fuel injection pump  a new premium highway tractor is introduced the vision by mack  mack builds  limited edition visions with black paint and cu