is looking for an obituary for a different person with this name mack wayne dennis obituary condolences dennis mack wayne  of flower mound tx died saturday september   mack was born february   in abilene tx to j paul and jean dennis he was a  graduate of abilene high school macks academic achievements included being one of the top  in his class of over  as well as being selected one of the top six student athletes his senior year mack graduated from abilene christian university in  where he was a member of subt social club he was a christian and a member of the bridgeway church in flower mound tx where he was drummer in their praise band mack served as the chief financial officer for billingsley company carrollton tx and has been with the company for the past  years he was an integral part of billingsleys working family as a loyal team member a mentor and most importantly a friend in gratitude and remembrance a plaque commemorating macks dedication spirit and leadership will be permanently placed at one arts plaza the memorial service is scheduled for  pm on thursday september  and will be held at one arts plaza located at the eastern edge of the dallas arts district at flora  routh httponeartsplazacomaboutmaphtml art mcneese of the bridgeway church will be officiating following the service family and friends are invited to stay and share in a time of fellowship and celebration of his life parking is available on both the garage and surface levels if you wish to share any stories memories or words of encouragement please visit httpwwwcaringbridgeorgvisitmackdennis mack is survived by his loving wife of  years lisa claire and two precious children luke parker  and mackenzie claire  two brothers jay and his wife merri along with their sons cole and jaron of euless tx and jon paul and his wife amy and their children colin and faith of sulphur springs tx his parents j paul and jean dennis of bedford tx funeral arrangements are being handled by flower mound family funeral home   an education contribution fund mack dennis childrens fund has been established at bank of america deposits can be made at any bank of america branch or they may mail checks to bank of america po box  dallas tx  ob obituaries notices published in dallas morning news from sept  to sept   read more remember share memories or express condolences below  entries the guest book is expired please restore the guest book to share in the life story for mack wayne dennis our continue love and prayers are with all of you we all miss mack and we realize that you are all in afrank and betty pope restore the guest book resources send funeral flowers donate to charity find advice  support funeral etiquette how to write a sympathy note  back to todays obituaries notify friends and family add the email addresses of friends or family members youd like to notify about this obituary to invalid to email from invalid from email message optional please provide me with special offers and discounts from legacycom and selected partners emails will be sent directly from legacycom we respect your privacy and will not sell your information to a third party you may opt out at any time see privacy policy for details your email was sent successfully return to the obituary send another email share there was an error sending your email please try again we apologize for the inconvenience mack products home mack products phone    moberly mo  home chevygmc dodge ford plymouth studebaker other contact our sister company welcome mack products founded in  mack products has devoted itself to providing the finest quality reproduction parts for antique pickups all pieces are authentic reproductions with mack products being careful to match all parts to the original material gauge form and finish search our online catalog for the individual parts you need for your complete original or custom restoration we supply truck bed parts for dodge willys studebaker and plymouth complete assembled beds or kits a